            <description><![CDATA[<h2>What&rsquo;s new in 0.1.0-b10</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>In-app updates.</strong> SipClient now checks for new
        releases automatically and offers to download and install them
        for you. You can also trigger a check manually from
        <em>SipClient &rarr; Check for Updates&hellip;</em>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Updates are signed end-to-end (Apple notarization plus a Sparkle
    EdDSA signature). If verification ever fails, the update is
    refused &mdash; you&rsquo;ll never end up running a tampered
    build.
</p>]]></description>
